        <bioghist id="ref83">
            <head>Biography</head>
            <p>
                <persname>Susan B. Aller</persname> is a children's and young adult's book author. Aller has authored over twenty works of fiction and non-fiction juvenile biographies including 
                <title render="italic">Emma and the Night Dogs</title>, 
                <title render="italic">J.M. Barrie: the Magic Behind Peter Pan</title>, 
                <title render="italic">Living With the Senecas: A Story About Mary Jemison</title>, 
                <title render="italic">Beyond Little Women: a Story about Louisa May Alcott</title>, 
                <title render="italic">Cristopher Columbus</title>, and 
                <title render="italic">Mark Twain</title>. As a native of 
                <geogname>Omaha, Nebraska</geogname>, Aller grew up loving books and spent hours in the public library and independent bookstores. Aller attended the 
                <corpname>University of Nebraska at Omaha</corpname> and majored in creative writting and English literature. Aller resides in 
                <geogname>West Hartford, Connecticut</geogname>, and is the mother to two sons and grandmother of six.</p>
        </bioghist>
